cff-version: 1.2.0

message: >-
  If you use Quality-Engineering-Skills in your research, teaching, or published work,
  please cite it using the metadata below. When referencing specific methodology content,
  also cite the underlying standard (ISO 9001:2015, IATF 16949:2016, AIAG-VDA FMEA 2019,
  VDA 6.3 2023, etc.) — this project implements those standards, it does not replace them.

title: "Quality-Engineering-Skills: Structured quality engineering skills and agents for AI"

abstract: >-
  Quality-Engineering-Skills is an open-source package of structured skill files and
  interactive agents that enable AI systems to apply quality engineering methodology
  accurately. The package covers 22 skills across 7 domains — problem solving (8D, 5-Why,
  DMAIC, Fishbone, Is/Is-Not, PDCA), risk analysis (PFMEA, DFMEA, Action Priority),
  planning (PPAP, APQP, Control Plan, DVP&R), measurement (MSA/Gauge R&R, SPC),
  documentation (NCR, CAR, 8D Customer Report), audit (ISO 9001, IATF 16949, VDA 6.3),
  and supplier quality (SCAR). Every skill maps to specific standard clauses and editions.
  The package also includes 8 interactive agents that guide practitioners step-by-step
  through structured quality processes with validation gates.
  Compatible with Claude Code, OpenAI ChatGPT, Cursor, Gemini CLI, Copilot Studio,
  and 20+ AI coding platforms.

